<font color="#FF0000">REMMINGTON RAIDERS</font><br>
<tt>Thu Jul 31  0:19:01 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Late one evening at sundown, I crashed smack in the middle of the famous 273rd Loc Ninh Regiment.  To make matters worse we splattered in the middle of an ancient cemetary.  Sir Charles came after us with a vengence.  Flying a Gunship, I had beau coup ammo.  I burned up several M-60 gun barrels while my wingman pumped his stuff into the surrounding jungle. A hundred PF's came to our rescue just to be slaughtered (80 of them) within spitting distance.  Just as it became dark a flare ship and a couple of Puffs showed up and laid on the heavy vulcan 20 mike mike stuff.  They came in very close.  Mud and crap was flying everywhere.  I stopped firing.  The tracers from my M-60 were pin pointing my position behind a very low dike.<br>
After three hours and some minutes of this the tide turned.  In the dark I heard helicopters coming.  My old Man had scrounged up every mechanic, cook, clerk and mail man in the area and they did an extremely dangerous night combat assault into that little hole in the jungle by the Dong Nai river... just for your brother, Ed.
